%description:

D3/D5(a) proving test, shape (i)+(iii-host): an in-path measurement layer
(inet.protocolelement.measurement.MeasurementLayer) is spliced into a
StandardHost at the transport/network boundary (the udp<->tn dispatcher
link), using the same NED extension + @reconnect technique as the
FlowMeasurementShowcase (MyStandardHost there, "MeasuredHost" here) -- there
is no built-in StandardHost parameter for this, so the insertion point is a
small NED subclass that reconnects two existing gates around a new
"like IMeasurementLayer" submodule.

This file's ini has two configs:
- [Config Baseline]: measurementLayer.typename = "" (IMeasurementLayer's
  @omittedTypename substitutes OmittedMeasurementLayer, a pure pass-through)
- [Config WithMeasurement]: measurementLayer.typename = "MeasurementLayer"
  (a real FlowMeasurementStarter/FlowMeasurementRecorder pair spliced in)

Both configs were run manually and produce IDENTICAL app-level output
(6 packets sent by the client -- the 6th is emitted right at the
sim-time-limit and never delivered, in both configs alike -- and 5 packets
received by the server -- see the scalar assertions below); this test
commits the WithMeasurement variant to prove insertion doesn't change
application-visible behavior.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%extraargs: -c WithMeasurement
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = Test
ned-path = .;../../../../src
sim-time-limit = 5ms
cmdenv-express-mode = false

#omnetpp 5.0 - 5.1 compatibility:
eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

*.client.hasTcp = false
*.client.hasSctp = false
*.client.hasQuic = false
*.server.hasTcp = false
*.server.hasSctp = false
*.server.hasQuic = false

*.client.numApps = 1
*.client.app[0].typename = "UdpSourceApp"
*.client.app[0].source.packetLength = 100B
*.client.app[0].source.productionInterval = 1ms
*.client.app[0].io.destAddress = "server"
*.client.app[0].io.destPort = 1000

*.server.numApps = 1
*.server.app[0].typename = "UdpSinkApp"
*.server.app[0].io.localPort = 1000

[Config Baseline]
*.client.measurementLayer.typename = ""
*.server.measurementLayer.typename = ""

[Config WithMeasurement]
*.client.measurementLayer.typename = "MeasurementLayer"
*.server.measurementLayer.typename = "MeasurementLayer"

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.node.inet.StandardHost;
import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv4.Ipv4NetworkConfigurator;
import inet.protocolelement.measurement.IMeasurementLayer;

module MeasuredHost extends StandardHost
{
    submodules:
        measurementLayer: <default("")> like IMeasurementLayer {
            @display("p=450,250");
        }
    connections:
        udp.ipOut --> { @reconnect; } --> measurementLayer.upperLayerIn if hasUdp;
        measurementLayer.lowerLayerOut --> { @reconnect; } --> tn.in[0] if hasUdp;
        udp.ipIn <-- { @reconnect; } <-- measurementLayer.upperLayerOut if hasUdp;
        measurementLayer.lowerLayerIn <-- { @reconnect; } <-- tn.out[0] if hasUdp;
}

network Test
{
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv4NetworkConfigurator {
            @display("p=300,100");
        }
        client: MeasuredHost {
            @display("p=150,250");
        }
        server: MeasuredHost {
            @display("p=450,250");
        }
    connections:
        client.ethg++ <--> { datarate = 100Mbps; delay = 10us; } <--> server.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: results/WithMeasurement-0.sca
scalar Test.client.app[0].io "packets sent" 6
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: results/WithMeasurement-0.sca
scalar Test.server.app[0].io "packets received" 5
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
